The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 21: Foreign direct investment plans of Citicorp International Finance and Suzuki Motor Corp were among the 25 proposals cleared today to bring in Rs 145.12 crore into the country. The proposals, cleared by finance minister P. Chidambaram, include a Rs 68.7-crore plan for setting up of a wholly-owned subsidiary by Italy-based Guarniflon Spa for research and development of polytetrafluoroethylene compounds, semi-finished and finished products. Suzuki will bring in Rs 12 crore for setting up a new joint venture in Haryana with a 30 per cent foreign equity participation. 

 New Delhi, April 21: The rate of inflation touched a 12-week high at 5.48 per cent for the week ended April 9 as vegetables, fruits, cooking gas and edible oils became costlier.

 New Delhi, April 21: Petroleum minister Mani Shankar Aiyar is likely to meet his cabinet colleague P. Chidambaram on Monday to push for duty cuts as a measure to avoid a rise in petrol and diesel prices.

 Pune, April 21: Avaya Inc has started the second phase of its India development centre, which would be its largest R amp;D unit outside the US. It would also hire 120 people by September.

 New Delhi, April 21: Kewal Handa will become the managing director of Pfizer India.




